{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow criminal injuries compensation for victims with unspent convictions",
        "additional_details": "For example, someone with a conviction for a crime such as theft could then be seriously injured in a violent attack, and not be eligible for compensation due to an unspent criminal conviction for an unrelated offence. I think this is unfair and many people are being let down by the system and left with no help or compensation for mental and physical injuries.",
        "background": "Change requirements of no unspent convictions on claiming criminal injury board compensation. Too many people who deserve assistance get no help due to previous misdemeanours.",
